content.Query:
exceptions
| where customDimensions contains "containers"
| extend pageUrl = tostring(customDimensions.urlHint)
| extend pageBase = tostring(split(pageUrl, '?')[0])
| where pageBase contains 'ininprodeusuxbase.' or pageBase contains 'afd.' or pageBase contains "monitoring."
// cloud ops tip 1
| where customDimensions.workspace_id !startswith '/subscriptions/692aea0b-2d89-4e7e-ae30-fffe40782ee2'
// Container Insights - Test - 1
| where customDimensions.workspace_id !startswith '/subscriptions/72c8e8ca-dc16-47dc-b65c-6b5875eb600a'
| extend handledAt = tostring(customDimensions.handledAt), httpStatusCode = tostring(customDimensions.httpStatusCode), details = tostring(customDimensions.details), user = tostring(customDimensions.user), exception = tostring(parse_json(tostring(type)).exception)
| where exception == '@getKubeConfig'
| extend WorkspaceName = tostring(todynamic(customDimensions).workspace_name), Version = tostring(split(operation_Name, '/', 5)[0])
| summarize Workspaces = dcount(WorkspaceName), Users = dcount(user_Id), Errors = count() by httpStatusCode, details, user, handledAt
| order by Workspaces desc, Users desc, Errors desc
| extend Affected_W_U = strcat(Workspaces, "/", Users)

inputs.name: Query
inputs.value:
let startTimestamp = ago(7d);
let endTimestamp = now();
exceptions
| where timestamp > startTimestamp
| where timestamp <= endTimestamp
| where customDimensions contains "containers"
| extend pageUrl = tostring(customDimensions.urlHint)
| extend pageBase = tostring(split(pageUrl, '?')[0])
// | where pageBase contains 'afd.'
| where pageBase contains 'ininprodeusuxbase.' or pageBase contains 'afd.' or pageBase contains "monitoring."
| extend MessageProperty = todynamic(outerMessage).exception.message, ErrorTextProperty = todynamic(outerMessage).exception._errorText, WorkspaceName = tostring(todynamic(customDimensions).workspace_name)
| extend Version = tostring(split(operation_Name, '/', 5)[0])
| extend PreMessage = tostring(iif(isempty(MessageProperty), ErrorTextProperty, MessageProperty))
| extend HttpRequestError = todynamic(todynamic(outerMessage).exception.httpRequestError)
| extend HttpError = iif(isnotempty(HttpRequestError), HttpRequestError, todynamic(todynamic(outerMessage).exception))
| extend HttpErrorStatusCode = toint(HttpError.status)
| extend HttpErrorStatusText = tostring(HttpError.statusText)
| extend HttpErrorResponseText = tostring(HttpError.responseText)
| extend HttpErrorResponseJson = parsejson(HttpErrorResponseText)
| extend PreMessage = iif(isempty(PreMessage) and isnotempty(HttpErrorStatusCode), strcat("Http ", HttpErrorStatusCode, " (", HttpErrorStatusText, "). Response: ", HttpErrorResponseText), PreMessage)
| extend Message = iif(isempty(PreMessage), "<Can't parse error object>", PreMessage)
| where Message != "<Can't parse error object>"
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 400 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.code == "SemanticError" and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.innererror.message contains "Failed to resolve table or column expression named 'KubeNodeInventory'", "Http 400 (Kube* TableNotFound)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 400 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.code == "SemanticError" and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.innererror.message contains "Failed to resolve table or column expression named 'KubePodInventory'", "Http 400 (Kube* TableNotFound)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 404 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.code == "WorkspaceNotFoundError", "Http 404 (WorkspaceNotFound)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 404 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.code == "ParentResourceNotFound", "Http 404 (WorkspaceNotFound)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 404 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.code == "ResourceGroupNotFound", "Http 404 (ResourceGroupNotFound)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 403 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.code == "InsufficientAccessError", "Http 403 (InsufficientAccess)", Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 503 and HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.code == "ServiceNotResponding", strcat("Http 503 (", HttpErrorResponseJson.error.innererror.message, ")"), Message)
| extend Message = iif(HttpErrorStatusCode == 502 and isnotempty(HttpErrorResponseJson.code),           strcat("Http 502 (", HttpErrorStatusText, ") <= ", HttpErrorResponseJson.code, " (", HttpErrorResponseJson.reason, ")"),           Message)
| extend Message = iif(tostring(todynamic(outerMessage).exception.textStatus) =~ 'timeout','Http timeout', Message)
| extend Message = iif(Message contains "does not have authorization to perform action 'Microsoft.ContainerService/managedClusters/listClusterUserCredential/action'", 'kubeConfig access denied', Message)
// cloud ops tip 1
| where customDimensions.workspace_id !startswith '/subscriptions/692aea0b-2d89-4e7e-ae30-fffe40782ee2'
// Container Insights - Test - 1
| where customDimensions.workspace_id !startswith '/subscriptions/72c8e8ca-dc16-47dc-b65c-6b5875eb600a'
| where todouble(severityLevel) > 2
| where tostring(customDimensions.handledAt) contains "pollserver" or tostring(customDimensions.handledAt) == "ContainerClusterPane" or tostring(customDimensions) contains "ContainerDeploymentList"
| summarize count() by bin(timestamp, 1h)
| render timechart
